73/*
74 * The tableindex array below is of size 256, one entry for each
75 * unsigned char value. The tableindex array elements are dependent on
76 * DNS_COMPRESS_TABLESIZE. The table was created using the following
77 * function.
78 *
79 * static void
80 * gentable(unsigned char *table) {
81 * unsigned int i;
82 * const unsigned int left = DNS_COMPRESS_TABLESIZE - 38;
83 * long r;
84 *
85 * for (i = 0; i < 26; i++) {
86 * table['A' + i] = i;
87 * table['a' + i] = i;
88 * }
89 *
90 * for (i = 0; i <= 9; i++)
91 * table['0' + i] = i + 26;
92 *
93 * table['-'] = 36;
94 * table['_'] = 37;
95 *
96 * for (i = 0; i < 256; i++) {
97 * if ((i >= 'a' && i <= 'z') ||
98 * (i >= 'A' && i <= 'Z') ||
99 * (i >= '0' && i <= '9') ||
100 * (i == '-') ||
101 * (i == '_'))
102 * continue;
103 * r = random() % left;
104 * table[i] = 38 + r;
105 * }
106 * }
107 */
108static unsigned char tableindex[256] = {
109 0x3e, 0x3e, 0x33, 0x2d, 0x30, 0x38, 0x31, 0x3c,
110 0x2b, 0x33, 0x30, 0x3f, 0x2d, 0x3c, 0x36, 0x3a,
111 0x28, 0x2c, 0x2a, 0x37, 0x3d, 0x34, 0x35, 0x2d,
112 0x39, 0x2b, 0x2f, 0x2c, 0x3b, 0x32, 0x2b, 0x39,
113 0x30, 0x38, 0x28, 0x3c, 0x32, 0x33, 0x39, 0x38,
114 0x27, 0x2b, 0x39, 0x30, 0x27, 0x24, 0x2f, 0x2b,
115 0x1a, 0x1b, 0x1c, 0x1d, 0x1e, 0x1f, 0x20, 0x21,
116 0x22, 0x3a, 0x29, 0x36, 0x31, 0x3c, 0x35, 0x26,
117 0x31, 0x00, 0x01, 0x02, 0x03, 0x04, 0x05, 0x06,
118 0x07, 0x08, 0x09, 0x0a, 0x0b, 0x0c, 0x0d, 0x0e,
119 0x0f, 0x10, 0x11, 0x12, 0x13, 0x14, 0x15, 0x16,
120 0x17, 0x18, 0x19, 0x3e, 0x3b, 0x39, 0x2f, 0x25,
121 0x27, 0x00, 0x01, 0x02, 0x03, 0x04, 0x05, 0x06,
122 0x07, 0x08, 0x09, 0x0a, 0x0b, 0x0c, 0x0d, 0x0e,
123 0x0f, 0x10, 0x11, 0x12, 0x13, 0x14, 0x15, 0x16,
124 0x17, 0x18, 0x19, 0x36, 0x3b, 0x2f, 0x2f, 0x2e,
125 0x29, 0x33, 0x2a, 0x36, 0x28, 0x3f, 0x2e, 0x29,
126 0x2c, 0x29, 0x36, 0x2d, 0x32, 0x3d, 0x33, 0x2a,
127 0x2e, 0x2f, 0x3b, 0x30, 0x3d, 0x39, 0x2b, 0x36,
128 0x2a, 0x2f, 0x2c, 0x26, 0x3a, 0x37, 0x30, 0x3d,
129 0x2a, 0x36, 0x33, 0x2c, 0x38, 0x3d, 0x32, 0x3e,
130 0x26, 0x2a, 0x2c, 0x35, 0x27, 0x39, 0x3b, 0x31,

132 0x34, 0x3f, 0x39, 0x2e, 0x38, 0x2b, 0x2c, 0x3e,
133 0x3b, 0x3b, 0x2d, 0x33, 0x3b, 0x3b, 0x32, 0x3d,

147isc_result_t
148dns_compress_init(dns_compress_t *cctx, int edns, isc_mem_t *mctx) {
149 REQUIRE(cctx != NULL);
150 REQUIRE(mctx != NULL); /* See: rdataset.c:towiresorted(). */
151
152 cctx->edns = edns;
153 cctx->mctx = mctx;
154 cctx->count = 0;
155 cctx->allowed = DNS_COMPRESS_ENABLED;
156
157 memset(&cctx->table[0], 0, sizeof(cctx->table));
158
159 cctx->magic = CCTX_MAGIC;
160
161 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
162}
163
164void
165dns_compress_invalidate(dns_compress_t *cctx) {
166 dns_compressnode_t *node;
167 unsigned int i;
168
169 REQUIRE(VALID_CCTX(cctx));
170
171 for (i = 0; i < DNS_COMPRESS_TABLESIZE; i++) {
172 while (cctx->table[i] != NULL) {
173 node = cctx->table[i];
174 cctx->table[i] = cctx->table[i]->next;
175 if ((node->offset & 0x8000) != 0)
176 isc_mem_put(cctx->mctx, node->r.base,
177 node->r.length);
178 if (node->count < DNS_COMPRESS_INITIALNODES)
179 continue;
180 isc_mem_put(cctx->mctx, node, sizeof(*node));
181 }
182 }
183
184 cctx->magic = 0;
185 cctx->allowed = 0;
186 cctx->edns = -1;
187}

190dns_compress_setmethods(dns_compress_t *cctx, unsigned int allowed) {

194 cctx->allowed |= (allowed & DNS_COMPRESS_ALL);
195}

232/*
233 * Find the longest match of name in the table.
234 * If match is found return true. prefix, suffix and offset are updated.
235 * If no match is found return false.
236 */
237bool
238dns_compress_findglobal(dns_compress_t *cctx, const dns_name_t *name,
239 dns_name_t *prefix, uint16_t *offset)
240{
241 dns_name_t tname;
242 dns_compressnode_t *node = NULL;
243 unsigned int labels, i, n;
244 unsigned int numlabels;
245 unsigned char *p;
246
247 REQUIRE(VALID_CCTX(cctx));
248 REQUIRE(dns_name_isabsolute(name) == true);
249 REQUIRE(offset != NULL);
250
251 if (ISC_UNLIKELY((cctx->allowed & DNS_COMPRESS_ENABLED) == 0))
252 return (false);
253
254 if (cctx->count == 0)
255 return (false);
256
257 labels = dns_name_countlabels(name);
258 INSIST(labels > 0);
259
260 dns_name_init(&tname, NULL);
261
262 numlabels = labels > 3U ? 3U : labels;
263 p = name->ndata;
264
265 for (n = 0; n < numlabels - 1; n++) {
266 unsigned char ch, llen;
267 unsigned int firstoffset, length;
268
269 firstoffset = (unsigned int)(p - name->ndata);
270 length = name->length - firstoffset;
271
272 /*
273 * We calculate the table index using the first
274 * character in the first label of the suffix name.
275 */
276 ch = p[1];
277 i = tableindex[ch];
278 if (ISC_LIKELY((cctx->allowed &
279 DNS_COMPRESS_CASESENSITIVE) != 0))
280 {
281 for (node = cctx->table[i];
282 node != NULL;
283 node = node->next)
284 {
285 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(node->name.length != length))
286 continue;
287
288 if (ISC_LIKELY(memcmp(node->name.ndata,
289 p, length) == 0))
290 goto found;
291 }
292 } else {
293 for (node = cctx->table[i];
294 node != NULL;
295 node = node->next)
296 {
297 unsigned int l, count;
298 unsigned char c;
299 unsigned char *label1, *label2;
300
301 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(node->name.length != length))
302 continue;
303
304 l = labels - n;
305 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(node->name.labels != l))
306 continue;
307
308 label1 = node->name.ndata;
309 label2 = p;
310 while (ISC_LIKELY(l-- > 0)) {
311 count = *label1++;
312 if (count != *label2++)
313 goto cont1;
314
315 /* no bitstring support */
316 INSIST(count <= 63);
317
318 /* Loop unrolled for performance */
319 while (ISC_LIKELY(count > 3)) {
320 c = maptolower[label1[0]];
321 if (c != maptolower[label2[0]])
322 goto cont1;
323 c = maptolower[label1[1]];
324 if (c != maptolower[label2[1]])
325 goto cont1;
326 c = maptolower[label1[2]];
327 if (c != maptolower[label2[2]])
328 goto cont1;
329 c = maptolower[label1[3]];
330 if (c != maptolower[label2[3]])
331 goto cont1;
332 count -= 4;
333 label1 += 4;
334 label2 += 4;
335 }
336 while (ISC_LIKELY(count-- > 0)) {
337 c = maptolower[*label1++];
338 if (c != maptolower[*label2++])
339 goto cont1;
340 }
341 }
342 break;
343 cont1:
344 continue;
345 }
346 }
347
348 if (node != NULL)
349 break;
350
351 llen = *p;
352 p += llen + 1;
353 }
354
355 found:
356 /*
357 * If node == NULL, we found no match at all.
358 */
359 if (node == NULL)
360 return (false);
361
362 if (n == 0)
363 dns_name_reset(prefix);
364 else
365 dns_name_getlabelsequence(name, 0, n, prefix);
366
367 *offset = (node->offset & 0x7fff);
368 return (true);
369}
370
371static inline unsigned int
372name_length(const dns_name_t *name) {
373 isc_region_t r;
374 dns_name_toregion(name, &r);
375 return (r.length);
376}

378void
379dns_compress_add(dns_compress_t *cctx, const dns_name_t *name,
380 const dns_name_t *prefix, uint16_t offset)
381{
382 dns_name_t tname, xname;
383 unsigned int start;
384 unsigned int n;
385 unsigned int count;
386 unsigned int i;
387 dns_compressnode_t *node;
388 unsigned int length;
389 unsigned int tlength;
390 uint16_t toffset;
391 unsigned char *tmp;
392 isc_region_t r;
393
394 REQUIRE(VALID_CCTX(cctx));
395 REQUIRE(dns_name_isabsolute(name));
396
397 if (ISC_UNLIKELY((cctx->allowed & DNS_COMPRESS_ENABLED) == 0))
398 return;
399
400 if (offset >= 0x4000)
401 return;
402 dns_name_init(&tname, NULL);
403 dns_name_init(&xname, NULL);
404
405 n = dns_name_countlabels(name);
406 count = dns_name_countlabels(prefix);
407 if (dns_name_isabsolute(prefix))
408 count--;
409 if (count == 0)
410 return;
411 start = 0;
412 dns_name_toregion(name, &r);
413 length = r.length;
414 tmp = isc_mem_get(cctx->mctx, length);
415 if (tmp == NULL)
416 return;
417 /*
418 * Copy name data to 'tmp' and make 'r' use 'tmp'.
419 */
420 memmove(tmp, r.base, r.length);
421 r.base = tmp;
422 dns_name_fromregion(&xname, &r);
423
424 if (count > 2U)
425 count = 2U;
426
427 while (count > 0) {
428 unsigned char ch;
429
430 dns_name_getlabelsequence(&xname, start, n, &tname);
431 /*
432 * We calculate the table index using the first
433 * character in the first label of tname.
434 */
435 ch = tname.ndata[1];
436 i = tableindex[ch];
437 tlength = name_length(&tname);
438 toffset = (uint16_t)(offset + (length - tlength));
439 if (toffset >= 0x4000)
440 break;
441 /*
442 * Create a new node and add it.
443 */
444 if (cctx->count < DNS_COMPRESS_INITIALNODES)
445 node = &cctx->initialnodes[cctx->count];
446 else {
447 node = isc_mem_get(cctx->mctx,
448 sizeof(dns_compressnode_t));
449 if (node == NULL)
450 break;
451 }
452 node->count = cctx->count++;
453 /*
454 * 'node->r.base' becomes 'tmp' when start == 0.
455 * Record this by setting 0x8000 so it can be freed later.
456 */
457 if (start == 0)
458 toffset |= 0x8000;
459 node->offset = toffset;
460 dns_name_toregion(&tname, &node->r);
461 dns_name_init(&node->name, NULL);
462 node->name.length = node->r.length;
463 node->name.ndata = node->r.base;
464 node->name.labels = tname.labels;
465 node->name.attributes = DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
466 node->next = cctx->table[i];
467 cctx->table[i] = node;
468 start++;
469 n--;
470 count--;
471 }
472
473 if (start == 0)
474 isc_mem_put(cctx->mctx, tmp, length);
475}
476
477void
478dns_compress_rollback(dns_compress_t *cctx, uint16_t offset) {
479 unsigned int i;
480 dns_compressnode_t *node;
481
482 REQUIRE(VALID_CCTX(cctx));
483
484 if (ISC_UNLIKELY((cctx->allowed & DNS_COMPRESS_ENABLED) == 0))
485 return;
486
487 for (i = 0; i < DNS_COMPRESS_TABLESIZE; i++) {
488 node = cctx->table[i];
489 /*
490 * This relies on nodes with greater offsets being
491 * closer to the beginning of the list, and the
492 * items with the greatest offsets being at the end
493 * of the initialnodes[] array.
494 */
495 while (node != NULL && (node->offset & 0x7fff) >= offset) {
496 cctx->table[i] = node->next;
497 if ((node->offset & 0x8000) != 0)
498 isc_mem_put(cctx->mctx, node->r.base,
499 node->r.length);
500 if (node->count >= DNS_COMPRESS_INITIALNODES)
501 isc_mem_put(cctx->mctx, node, sizeof(*node));
502 cctx->count--;
503 node = cctx->table[i];
504 }
505 }
506}

512void
513dns_decompress_init(dns_decompress_t *dctx, int edns,
514 dns_decompresstype_t type) {
515
516 REQUIRE(dctx != NULL);
517 REQUIRE(edns >= -1 && edns <= 255);
518
519 dctx->allowed = DNS_COMPRESS_NONE;
520 dctx->edns = edns;
521 dctx->type = type;
522 dctx->magic = DCTX_MAGIC;
523}

525void
526dns_decompress_invalidate(dns_decompress_t *dctx) {
527
528 REQUIRE(VALID_DCTX(dctx));
529
530 dctx->magic = 0;
531}

533void
534dns_decompress_setmethods(dns_decompress_t *dctx, unsigned int allowed) {
535
536 REQUIRE(VALID_DCTX(dctx));
537
538 switch (dctx->type) {
539 case DNS_DECOMPRESS_ANY:
540 dctx->allowed = DNS_COMPRESS_ALL;
541 break;
542 case DNS_DECOMPRESS_NONE:
543 dctx->allowed = DNS_COMPRESS_NONE;
544 break;
545 case DNS_DECOMPRESS_STRICT:
546 dctx->allowed = allowed;
547 break;
548 }
549}
550
551unsigned int
552dns_decompress_getmethods(dns_decompress_t *dctx) {
553
554 REQUIRE(VALID_DCTX(dctx));
555
556 return (dctx->allowed);
557}
